newsitem.title: USA: FOB Gulf Grain-Soy mostly firmer, corn, wheat flat.
newsitem.headline: FOB Gulf Grain-Soy mostly firmer, corn, wheat flat.

text.p: FOB Gulf soybeans continued firmer on Thursday while corn and wheat values were steady.
The lack of export activity was noted by dealers.

But interest for soybeans emerged from the Far East. Taiwan's Breakfast Soybean Procurement Association plans to tender on Friday for two shipments of U.S. soybeans totalling 108,000 tonnes, traders said.

The first shipment would be for delivery from the U.S. Gulf of Mexico November 10-24 or from the Pacific Northwest November 25-December 9. The second would be for delivery from the U.S. Gulf December 5-19 or from the Pacific Northwest December 20-January 3, they said.
Dealers quoted the following afternoon FOB U.S. Gulf values, basis Chicago futures, except hard red winter wheat basis Kansas City. (In cents per bushel).
